{
  "stem": "3690.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We didn't know what happened to them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So, but it came out every-- once a week, it came out, a Red Cross paper, which was issued by the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it used to be alphabetically, under sequence-- alphabetically, names and people's names and addresses-- who survived and from which town they come and where they are now.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So, sure enough, I found Julia Spitz [SOBBING] and-- and Livia Spitz and [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Gretchen ?] Spitz survived in Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[SOBBING] And they got taken to Sweden, by the Swedish Red Cross, to a sanatorium.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were very sick.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[SOBBING] So I found out that my mother survived and my two sisters.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[CRYING] Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And, [SOBBING] right away, I tried to organize to see if I could go to Sweden and visit them and try to help them or do what I-- whatever I can do.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So it wasn't that easy, but, later on, I-- I got somehow together a-- a passport which they would let me go to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Your brother went with you?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't go to Sweden yet, because we didn't have the-- the sponsor, anything.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, everything had to--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, and then, the next day, I found another US paper, which says, Joseph Spitz survived-- in the Red Cross paper-- in Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he is in a hospital.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he has-- he has Fleck typhus, so he's all swollen, his legs are swollen and his body from typhus.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He has-- I don't know if you know what typhus is.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I found out, oh, my father [SOBBING] is alive, too.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[CRYING] So, [SOBBING] so I started asking about the rest of the family.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I said, did you heard about Walter Spitz, my brother?",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
